          "parts": [
            "Here’s a polished draft you can adapt for submitting your dissertation to your committee members:  \n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Submission of Dissertation for Committee Review  \n\nDear [Committee Member’s Name / Committee Members],  \n\nI am pleased to share with you the completed draft of my dissertation, titled *“[Your Dissertation Title Here]”*. This version incorporates the revisions and feedback received during my proposal and subsequent meetings. I am submitting it for your review ahead of my defense.  \n\nPlease find the dissertation attached [or: uploaded at the following link: **[insert link]**]. I welcome any comments or suggestions you may have and will incorporate them as I prepare for the defense.  \n\nThank you very much for your guidance and support throughout this process. I truly appreciate the time and effort you dedicate to reviewing my work.  \n\nBest regards,  \n[Your Full Name]  \nPh.D. Candidate  \nSchool of Computing, University of Utah  \n\n---\n\nWould you like me to also draft a **more formal version** (aligned with typical defense submission etiquette), or a **slightly warmer version** that emphasizes your appreciation for their mentorship?"
          ]
